  "text": "We obtained this by multiplying the total charge billed to the patient with the hospital's discount rate for privately insured patients. As carried out in previous literature, the discount rate for privately insured patients at each hospital was calculated using the formula: (gross inpatient revenue+gross outpatient revenue−contractual adjustments)/(gross inpatient revenue+gross outpatient revenue). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] We obtained these amounts through the 2011 OSHPD financial files for each hospital.",
